com.concordium.sdk.crypto.wallet.web3Id

Class IdentityClaims

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.concordium.sdk.crypto.wallet.web3Id.IdentityClaims
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SubjectClaims

    public class IdentityClaims
extends Object
implements SubjectClaims
    Statements requesting proofs from identity credentials issued by identity providers.

    Although it is called "identity claims", either identity credential, or account credential, or both can be used to prove these claims, depending on source.

      • canBeProvedBy

        public boolean canBeProvedBy(IdentityObject idObject,
                             UInt32 ipIdentity)
        Parameters:
        idObject - identity itself or a particular account identity
        ipIdentity - index of the identity provider that issued this identity
        Returns:
        whether the given identity itself or an account created from it can actually prove these claims. The identity must prove all the statements and it must be issued by one of the allowed issuers.

      • getIdentityProofInput

        public IdentityClaimsIdentityProofInput getIdentityProofInput(Network network,
                                                              IdentityProviderInfo ipInfo,
                                                              Map<String,AnonymityRevokerInfo> arsInfos,
                                                              IdentityObject idObject,
                                                              BLSSecretKey idCredSec,
                                                              BLSSecretKey prfKey,
                                                              String blindingRandomness)
        Prove these claims with an identity credential.
        Parameters:
        network - network on which the identity is issued
        ipInfo - identity provider that issued the identity, stored in the wallet or fetched from a node
        arsInfos - anonymity revokers of the identity provider, stored in the wallet or fetched from a node
        idObject - identity itself, stored in the wallet after creation or recovery
        idCredSec - cred sec for the identity, derived with the HD wallet
        prfKey - PRF key for the identity, derived with the HD wallet
        blindingRandomness - signature blinding randomness for the identity, derived with the HD wallet
        Returns:
        input needed to create a verifiable presentation
        See Also:
        Check if identity credentials are even accepted, Check if a particular identity can prove the claims, Fetch identity providers, Fetch anonymity revokers, Derive ID cred sec, Derive PRF key, Derive signature blinding randomness
